==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Motorize
<hw>Mo"tor*ize</hw> <pr>(m⟦omac⟧"t⟦etil⟧r*⟦imac⟧z)</pr>, <pos>v.
t.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Motor</ets> + <ets>-ize</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To substitute motor-driven vehicles, or automobiles, for the horses
and horse-drawn vehicles of (a fire department, city, etc.).</def>
<mark>[archaic]</mark> -- <wordforms><wf>Mo`tor*i*za"tion</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>to equip (a piece of machinery) with a
motor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>to provide with automobiles or other motor vehicles;
<as>as, a <ex>motorized</ex> army division</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mechanize.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>motorized</ent>⟦br⟧
